1.) Difference between plan and apply?
Solution:- 
Terraform plan compares current state(tfsate) and desired config(.tf file) while terraform apply executes the plan and calls provider APIs. 
In simple terms if you want to see what changes will happen before we do "terraform apply", we do terraform plan it gives us a rough idea that what all resources will be added or destroyed.

2.)What is stored in terraform.tfstate?
Solution:- terraform.tfstate contains:

Resource IDs (real infra mapping)

Attributes (IP, names, metadata)

Dependency data

Provider info

# It is the source of truth mapping config → real world

3.) Why does Terraform need providers?
Solution:- Providers are what let terraform create and manage real resources by connecting it to external systems.

4.) What happens if state file is deleted?
Solution:-
If deleted:

Terraform loses mapping

Thinks nothing exists

Will try to recreate everything

Can cause:

duplicate infra

conflicts

outages

5.) Is Terraform imperative or declarative? Why?
Solution:- Terraform is declarative because you define the desired end state, and it figures out how to achieve it automatically.
